Asplenium ruta-muraria is a species of fern.
It has small, delicate fronds that grow in a rosette shape.
The fronds are a bright green color and have a smooth, glossy texture.
The leaf blades are usually oblong or lance-shaped.
The fronds can grow up to 20 cm tall and have a triangular shape.
It is commonly found growing on walls, rocks, and cliffs in temperate regions.
Asplenium ruta-muraria is often prized by gardeners for its beauty and ease of cultivation.
